@multiarg futon7/devmap
@title FUTON7 Development Map — Transparent Knowledge Economy
@audience futon-devs, sphere-architects, future-you
@tone formal-analytic
@style roadmap
@factor Civic equanimity (upa-upekkhā)
@IFR: FUTON7 is a new form of knowledge economy that adds transparency to the
regular economy by tracking costs, relationships, and externalities that current
systems obscure.
@state Landscape intelligence operational: 10 probes across 3 proximity levels;
lead report generated (M-f7-lead-report COMPLETE); probe generation from
futon3a concept graph (M-futon3x-e2e L5). Hyperreal operates as informal seed
institution; Gravpad conceptualised but not implemented.
@next Define Gravpad MVP; structure first scenario simulation; document Hyperreal
as explicit F7 prototype; integrate concept-graph probes into regular landscape scans.

## The Argument

FUTON7 is a new form of knowledge economy that adds transparency to the regular
economy by tracking costs, relationships, and externalities that current systems
obscure. Hyperreal Enterprises is a seed institution testing these ideas in real
economic terrain. Gravpad does to the web what street art does to cities—adding
commentary and transparency without permission. Mathematical models from F6 feed
into scenario simulations that test future structures before implementation.


! instantiated-by: Prototype 0 — Hyperreal Enterprises as Seed Institution [⌛️/己 💫/业]
  :maturity :greenfield
  :depends-on []
  :evidence-for-active [Hyperreal operating; governance documented; economic model tested]

  + context: F7 needs a living prototype, not just theory.
  + IF: You want to test transparent knowledge economy ideas in real conditions
  + HOWEVER: Abstract designs need concrete instantiation
  + THEN: Position Hyperreal explicitly as F7's seed institution practicing transparent governance, pattern-based documentation, and consulting as economic model
  + BECAUSE: A concrete institution anchors abstractions into lived practice

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[Hyperreal operates as consulting practice]
    evidence[Values and narrative documented]
    evidence[Client-based R&D loops exist]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Document Hyperreal governance explicitly as F7 prototype]
    next[Track economic flows transparently]
    next[Iterate institutional design based on experience]

  :success-criteria
    pass[Hyperreal operates sustainably]
    pass[Governance transparent and documented]
    pass[Learnings feed back into F7 design]
    fail[Institution collapses or becomes opaque]

  :psr-example "Selected Hyperreal as seed because living prototypes test theory"
  :pur-template "Hyperreal period {{period}}, clients: {{count}}, governance updates: {{updates}}"


! instantiated-by: Prototype 1 — Gravpad [👎/引 ⛲️/广]
  :maturity :greenfield
  :depends-on []
  :evidence-for-active [Gravpad deployed; web annotation operational]

  + context: Gravpad does to the web what street art does to cities.
  + IF: You want to add commentary and transparency to the web without permission
  + HOWEVER: Current web infrastructure serves platform owners, not users
  + THEN: Build Gravpad as web annotation layer that adds traceability, commentary, and accountability information to existing web content
  + BECAUSE: Transparency infrastructure should not require permission from those being made transparent

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[Arxana provides annotation model]
    evidence[Web annotation standards exist]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Define Gravpad MVP]
    next[Build annotation layer]
    next[Test on real web content]
    next[Document supply chain / externality use cases]

  :success-criteria
    pass[Annotations attach to web content]
    pass[No permission required from target sites]
    pass[Traceability information visible to users]
    fail[Annotations blocked or invisible]

  :psr-example "Selected Gravpad for transparency because street art doesn't ask permission"
  :pur-template "Gravpad annotation {{url}}, type: {{type}}, visible: {{yes|no}}"


! instantiated-by: Prototype 2 — Scenario Simulations [🚞/习 🔸/扎]
  :maturity :greenfield
  :depends-on [f6/P9]
  :evidence-for-active [Scenario bundles defined; simulations run; results documented]

  + context: Future structures should be tested before implementation.
  + IF: You want to prototype civic and economic forms before committing
  + HOWEVER: Abstract philosophy does not test well
  + THEN: Develop scenario bundles tied to F6 mathematical models; run simulations; document results and learnings
  + BECAUSE: Scenario practice turns philosophy into actionable design

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[F6 provides mathematical models]
    evidence[Scenario concepts identified]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Define 2-3 scenario bundles]
    next[Tie scenarios to F6 models]
    next[Run simulations]
    next[Document learnings]

  :success-criteria
    pass[Scenarios defined with clear parameters]
    pass[Simulations produce testable results]
    pass[Learnings inform F7 design]
    fail[Scenarios remain abstract]

  :psr-example "Selected scenario simulations for testing because future structures need prototyping"
  :pur-template "Scenario {{name}}, model: {{model}}, result: {{outcome}}"


! instantiated-by: Prototype 3 — Landscape Intelligence (Probes + Lead Report) [👓/见 🌏/门]
  :maturity :active
  :depends-on []
  :evidence-for-active [10 probes across 3 proximity levels run; lead report generated; concept-graph probe generation operational]

  + context: F7 needs concrete market intelligence, not just theory.
  + IF: You want to know where the futon stack intersects commercial demand
  + HOWEVER: Manual market research is episodic and subjective
  + THEN: Build automated landscape probes (GitHub search + scoring), generate consulting lead reports, and generate new probes from the concept graph (futon3a meme.db)
  + BECAUSE: Evidence-based market intelligence grounds F7's transparency thesis in real demand signals

  + EVIDENCE:
    evidence[futon7/src/f7/probes.clj: 10 hand-crafted probes across domain/adjacent/orthogonal proximity]
    evidence[futon7/src/f7/probe_gen.clj: generates probes from futon3a concept graph (M-futon3x-e2e L5)]
    evidence[futon7/data/results/generated-probes.edn: 7 concept-graph probes across 7 areas]
    evidence[M-f7-lead-report COMPLETE: human-readable lead report with commercial signal scoring]
    evidence[futon7/bb.edn: probe-gen task added for babashka execution]

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    next[Integrate concept-graph probes into regular landscape scan schedule]
    next[Add probe result persistence and trend tracking]
    next[Generate second lead report and compare evolution]

  :success-criteria
    pass[Probes generate actionable leads with commercial scoring]
    pass[Concept-graph probes cover areas hand-crafted probes miss]
    pass[Lead report readable by non-technical audience]
    fail[Probes return noise or lead report is not actionable]

  :psr-example "Selected landscape probes for market intelligence because evidence-based signals beat intuition"
  :pur-template "Probe run {{name}}, results: {{count}}, leads: {{leads}}, proximity: {{level}}"
